<TITLE> India inflation to ease to 5-6 pct in a year: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Wed Aug 27, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India's annual inflation rate will fall to 5 to 6 percent in the next 12 months, helped by the central bank's recent policy tightenings, the finance minister's chief economic adviser said on Wednesday. Inflation could fall sharply if oil prices recede, Arvind Virmani told reporters. Oil was trading around $118 a barrel on Wednesday, well below a record peak above $147 set last month. India's annual wholesale price-based inflation rate rose to 12.63 percent on Aug. 9
